import { Meta } from "@storybook/addon-docs/blocks";
import useClipboard from 'util/storybook-docs/useClipboard';
import useToggleHover from 'util/storybook-docs/useToggleHover';
import cx from 'classnames';
import { TableLayout } from 'util/storybook-docs/Table';

export const importPath = iconName => (
  `import ${iconName}Icon from '@cbinsights/fds/lib/icons/react/${iconName}Icon';`
);

export const Icon = ({ name, svg }) => {
  const [copiedText, copyToClipboard] = useClipboard();
  const [isHovered, toggleHover] = useToggleHover();
  return (
    <li>
      <div
        onClick={() => copyToClipboard(importPath(name))}
        className={cx('rounded--all', {
          'elevation--1': isHovered,
        })}
        onMouseEnter={toggleHover}
        onMouseLeave={toggleHover}
      >
        <div
          dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: svg }}
        />
        <span
          className={cx("copyNotice", { 'display--block': isHovered })}
        >
          {copiedText ? <b>Copied to Clipboard</b> : 'Copy to Clipboard'}
        </span>
        <p className="wrap--singleLine--truncate type--data">{name}</p>
      </div>
    </li>
  )
}

<Meta title="Icons/Icons" />

# Icons

FDS provides an icon set in `svg`, `png`, and React component formats. This page covers
React component usage. For more details about using other formats please see the [icons
README](https://github.com/cbinsights/form-design-system/tree/master/src/icons#usage).

<TableLayout
  headers={['Prop', 'Type', 'Default', 'Description']}
  rows={[
      ['`color`', '`String`', '`COLOR_CHARCOAL`', 'Color of `fill` for SVG'],
      ['`size`', 'One of: `\'xs\' | \'s\' | \'m\' | \'l\' | \'xl\'`', 's', 'Standard media size of icon'],
      ['`customSize`', '`Number`', '`-`', 'Sets a non-standard size for the icon. Prefer using the size prop.'],
  ]}
/>

Clicking on an icon below will copy the import statement.
